# Lazy evaluation, in depth

## The reference

- **Transformations — lazy** · append to the plan, return a DataFrame
  - `select`, `filter`, `withColumn`, `groupBy`, `join`, `orderBy`
- **Actions — eager** · trigger DAG execution, return a value/file/output
  - `show`, `count`, `collect`, `take`, `first`, `write`

## What waiting buys Spark

- **Push filters early** — run next to the scan, so less data flows
- **Prune projections** — drop unreferenced columns before reading
- **Fuse operations** — narrow steps collapse into one loop (codegen)
- **Skip everything** — no action, no work

Every win is possible **only because Spark waited**.
